Frequently Asked Questions for Aurvista Gold Corp (TSE:AVA)
What is Aurvista Gold Corp's stock symbol?

Aurvista Gold Corp trades on the Tornton Stock Exchange (TSX) under the ticker symbol "AVA."



Who are some of Aurvista Gold Corp's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Aurvista Gold Corp include National Grid Transco, PLC (NGG), National Grid plc (NG), Sempra Energy (SRE), PPL Corporation (PPL), Avangrid (AGR), Ameren Corporation (AEE), CMS Energy Corporation (CMS), CenterPoint Energy (CNP), Centrica PLC (CNA), NiSource (NI), MDU Resources Group (MDU), Black Hills Corporation (BKH), Pennon Group plc (PNN), Empire District Electric Co (EDE) and Wec Acquisition Corp (TEG).



Who are Aurvista Gold Corp's key executives?

Aurvista Gold Corp's management team includes the folowing people: Scott L. Morris, Chairman of the Board, President, Chief Executive OfficerMark T. Thies, Chief Financial Officer, Senior Vice President, TreasurerMarian M. Durkin, Senior Vice President, Chief Compliance Officer, General Counsel, Corporate SecretaryJason R. Thackston, Senior Vice President, Vice President - Energy ResourcesKaren S. Feltes, Senior Vice President - Human ResourcesDennis P. Vermillion, Senior Vice PresidentRyan L. Krasselt, Principal Accounting Officer, Vice President, ControllerJames M. Kensok, Chief Information Officer, Vice PresidentKevin J. Christie, Vice President - Customer SolutionsDavid J. Meyer, Chief Counsel - Regulatory and Governmental Affairs, Vice President



How do I buy Aurvista Gold Corp stock? 

Shares of Aurvista Gold Corp and other Canadian stocks can be purchased through online brokerage accounts that support trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange (TSX). Brokers that permit trading on the TSX include Fidelity, Interactive Brokers, PennTrade and Charles Schwab.


